# Homelab

Just a small homelab I've been building and tinkering with at home — mostly 
for learning, but also because I genuinely use a couple of these services 
day to day. Documenting it here as I go.

## What's in here

### 🖥️ Proxmox + Nextcloud
An old laptop that got a second life as a Proxmox box, running Nextcloud 
so I've got my own private cloud storage instead of relying on someone 
else's servers. There's an external hard drive attached for the actual 
storage.

📄 [Full writeup](docs/proxmox-nextcloud-setup.md)

### 🛡️ Pi-hole (Raspberry Pi 5)
A Raspberry Pi 5 running Pi-hole to block ads and trackers network-wide. 
It works, I got it running properly, but honestly I haven't used it much 
lately — still counts as a fun build though.

📄 [Full writeup](docs/pihole-setup.md)

## Why bother writing this up
Mostly so I don't forget what I did and why, six months from now when 
something breaks. Also figured it's worth sharing in case any of it's 
useful to someone else poking around with their own setup.

## Current status
| Component | Status |
|---|---|
| Proxmox + Nextcloud | ✅ Up and running, actually used |
| Pi-hole | 🟡 Working, just not actively used right now |

